
cat something | more [This prints the file in small groups, allowing you to easily look through huge files].

===

cat -b [prints the file, with line numbers].

===

head fileName [it shows th beginning few lines of the file].

===

head -3 fileName [it shows the first 3 lines of the file].

===

tail fileName [it shows the end few[5] lines of the file, kind of like opposite of the head].

===

less fileName [thora thora karke dikhayega file ko :) ].

===

vi [opens an empty file]

to exit the editor you write

esc + :q

===

use :q! for force exit.
